Description: Ostracon, fragment of the body of a pale-red pottery vessel, the fabric is grey in section and contains many small white inclusions, the exterior is covered with a cream-coloured slip and faint traces of five lines of black-painted demotic text.
Bibliographic references: Trismegistos / An interdisciplinary portal of papyrological and epigraphic resources (393786) (http://www.trismegistos.org/text/393786)
